cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.NE 

This paper deals with reachability analysis and risk measures for stochastic dynamic systems, which are typically studied in the fields of control theory and robotics (cs.SY, cs.RO). The use of Markov Decision Processes (MDPs) and algorithms for approximation also suggest a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the computation of risk measures, which is a topic in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG, cs.NE).
